failed_tasks.reason: Critique: Try "look at rubber mat" or "examine rubber mat" to prompt a more detailed description. If that fails, try "move mat" or "look under mat" for further interaction.

Critique: Try moving to the location where the front door is visible (e.g., "look at door" or "go to front door"), then use "open door" again. If the door is boarded, ensure you have removed all obstacles first.
Critique: Try "examine jewel-encrusted egg" or "look at jewel-encrusted egg" to prompt a more detailed description from the game.
Critique: Try exploring nearby areas or using "look" or "examine" commands to locate the grating before attempting to open it. Ensure you are in the correct location where the grating is visible.
Critique: Try using "examine birds nest" or "look at birds nest" exactly, or try examining it in a different location. Sometimes the game requires the full object name or a specific context.
Critique: Try "open mailbox" again while you are at the location with the mailbox, and look for a message confirming it is open or describing its contents.

Critique: Try exploring other directions or examining your surroundings for alternate paths to the clearing. Use "look" to find possible exits, or try "go northeast," "go southeast," or similar commands if available.
Critique: Try using "climb up", "climb canyon", or "go up" again. If the game still doesn't respond, look for objects or features (like vines or ledges) that might help you climb.

Critique: Try using "examine egg" or "look at egg" again, or check if the egg is called something else in the game. You may also need to be in a different location or drop and pick up the egg before examining it.

Critique: Try "examine egg" or "look at egg" again to see if a more detailed description appears, or check if the egg can be opened in a different way. If the egg is not readable, the task may not be possible.
Critique: Try "go southwest" or "sw" again from your current location, or look for a location where a narrow path leads southwest and take that direction.

Critique: Try using "open jewel-encrusted egg" or "examine egg closely" to see if a more specific command is needed to open it. Some games require a special action or tool—consider examining the egg for hidden mechanisms or using another item on it.

Critique: Try examining the rainbow for clues, or look for another way to cross—perhaps a specific command like "walk on rainbow" or "climb rainbow" is needed. Consider if an item or action is required to make the rainbow crossable.

Critique: Try specifying the object more clearly, such as "climb down ledge" or "climb down into canyon," or look for an obvious path or exit (e.g., "go down" or "descend"). Use "look" to see if there is a more specific feature to interact with.
Critique: Try "look at egg closely" or "inspect jewel-encrusted egg" to see if a more detailed description is available.
Critique: Try using "look at egg" or "examine egg" again, or check if the egg is called something else in the game. You may also need to open or manipulate the egg before examining it.

Critique: Try "look at nest" or "examine birds nest" again, or simply "look" while the nest is present in the room, as some games require the object to be placed in the environment rather than in your inventory for a detailed description.
Critique: Try examining the nest more closely or using commands like "search nest" or "look under nest" to discover if it can be opened or if it contains anything.

Critique: Try "open grating" again and look for a message confirming it is open, or examine the grating after attempting to open it to check its status. If it is locked, try to find a key or another way to open it.

WELCOME TO ZORK

    ZORK is a game of adventure, danger, and low cunning.  In it you will explore some of the most amazing territory ever seen by mortal man.  Hardened adventurers have run screaming from the terrors contained within!

    In ZORK the intrepid explorer delves into the forgotten secrets of a lost labyrinth deep in the bowels of the earth, searching for vast treasures long hidden from prying eyes, treasures guarded by fearsome monsters and diabolical traps!

    No PDP-10 should be without one!

    ZORK was created at the MIT Laboratory for Computer Science, by Tim Anderson, Marc Blank, Bruce Daniels, and Dave Lebling.  It was inspired by the ADVENTURE game of Crowther and Woods, and the long tradition of fantasy and science fiction adventure.  ZORK was originally written in MDL (alias MUDDLE).  The current version was translated from MDL into Inform by Ethan Dicks <erd@infinet.com>.

Up a Tree
You are about 10 feet above the ground nestled among some large branches.  The nearest branch above you is above your reach.
On the branch is a small birds nest.
In the bird's nest is a large egg encrusted with precious jewels, apparently scavenged somewhere by a childless songbird.  The egg is covered with fine gold inlay, and ornamented in lapis lazuli and mother-of-pearl.  Unlike most eggs, this one is hinged and has a delicate looking clasp holding it closed.  The egg appears extremely fragile.

Canyon View
You are at the top of the Great Canyon on its south wall.  From here there is a marvelous view of the Canyon and parts of the Frigid River upstream.  Across the canyon, the walls of the White Cliffs still appear to loom far above.  Following the Canyon upstream (north and northwest), Aragain Falls may be seen, complete with rainbow. Fortunately, my vision is better than average and I can discern the top of the Flood Control Dam #3 far to the distant north.  To the west and south can be seen an immense forest, stretching for miles around.  It is possible to climb down into the canyon from here.

Rocky Ledge
You are on a ledge about halfway up the wall of the river canyon. You can see from here that the main flow from Aragain Falls twists along a passage which it is impossible to enter.  Below you is the canyon bottom.  Above you is more cliff, which still appears climbable.

>                                                                                                                                Rocky LedgeScore: 5Moves: 197

Canyon View

>                                                                                                                                Canyon ViewScore: 5Moves: 198

Canyon View
You are at the top of the Great Canyon on its south wall.  From here there is a marvelous view of the Canyon and parts of the Frigid River upstream.  Across the canyon, the walls of the White Cliffs still appear to loom far above.  Following the Canyon upstream (north and northwest), Aragain Falls may be seen, complete with rainbow. Fortunately, my vision is better than average and I can discern the top of the Flood Control Dam #3 far to the distant north.  To the west and south can be seen an immense forest, stretching for miles around.  It is possible to climb down into the canyon from here.
